The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Microsoft: EU ruling flawed

 Luxembourg, April 24 (Reuters): Microsoft told a special 13-judge court today the European Commission made fundamental errors in deciding that the company illegally tied Windows Media Player to its near-monopoly operating system.

 That theory is flawed at every step, Microsoft lawyer Jean-Francois Bellis told Europes second-highest court, the Court of First Instance, in opening remarks during the software giants challenge to the landmark 2004 decision.

 Instead, he said, consumers had benefited from Microsofts improved Windows. 




